      "abstract": "The article deals with theoretical and methodological problem \u2013 the contribution of history of psychology and historical psychology to studying of spiritual/moral sphere of human existence and religious experience. Such knowledge introduces the psychological science to ontology of human psyche, which presupposes its transcendent dimension and \u00abmetaphysical/universal\u00bb foundations. The importance of the Russian philosophical and religious tradition is emphasized. Based on the Orthodox-Christian heritage, in particular, on patristic anthropological and psychological ideas, the description of multilayered inner world of human being is proposed. Such description includes the following \u00ablayers\u00bb around the core \u2013 the \u00abspiritual self\u00bb. Shell-1\u00bb \u2013 reflection of the macro-social world by personality. \u00abShell-2\u00bb \u2013 product of scenario programming in the primary family and immediate environment outside it. \u00abShell-3\u00bb is associated with images of a person\u2019s physical physicality and its pneumo-psycho-somatic connections. \u00abShell-4\u00bb consists of a human being ideas about himself, the world and place in the Universe; it includes a pronounced ideological aspect. The main characteristic of the \u00abshell-5\u00bb is a person\u2019s experience (vague or clear) of some \u00abinvisible spiritual and metaphysical forces of the soul\u00bb presence. \u00abShell-6\u00bb expresses religious/mystical experience of people. The \u00abcore\u00bb of the \u00abshells\u00bb system is integral indivisible human soul associated with the \u00abspiritual self\u00bb. The proposed description of inner world of a personality helps psychological correction, contributes to form a holistic perception of uniqueness of inner world, with its connections with group consciousness of various levels and the Universe. Some research tasks are set for future studying. Particularly correlating the proposed model with