      "year": 2025,
      "abstract": "The text is devoted to reflection on the limitations of the understanding of justice in mainstream economics. The analysis covers the epistemological limitations of the post-marginalist approach and the reductionism in the field of social ontology, which does not allow for taking into account the complexity and richness of the life of real communities. Based on selected examples, the Christian tradition and classical political economy are presented as alternative approaches, which \u2013 despite the differences that divide them \u2013 operated with a holistic, integral understanding of the term. The author tries to show that regardless of whether the foundation of thinking was a metaphysical, external order or immanent utilitarian ethics, the discussed concepts were characterized in many aspects by a deeper understanding of multidimensional social reality than the formalist-transactional paradigm that has dominated since the end of the 19th century.",
